remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoderFrame` pairs an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> with a display duration, and is
used as an element in the frame sequence passed to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame},SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions)>.

Convenience constructors accept an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKBitmap> or an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKImage>
and automatically obtain the corresponding pixmap.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var frames = new SKWebpEncoderFrame[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap1, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bitmap3, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(200)),
};

using var data = SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(frames, SKWebpEncoderOptions.Default);
if (data != null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("animation.webp", data.ToArray());
```
